1
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:13,333
You're the one who brought us
here.

2
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:16,867
Like you, I'm just trying
to find them.

3
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:18,367
Can you stop being suspicious
of me?

4
00:00:18,433 --> 00:00:20,367
What if we're out of time?

5
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:22,033
I might not find my daughter.

6
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:25,800
I'll make sure that this time,
we'll be together forever.

7
00:00:25,867 --> 00:00:27,633
That reminds me of my twins.

8
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:28,933
Emma has a twin?

9
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:31,733
My eldest are twins.

10
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:33,867
They're a year older than Emma.

11
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:35,433
Doctor of medicine?

12
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,033
What kind of doctor are they?

13
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:38,867
They're heart specialists.

14
00:00:38,933 --> 00:00:40,433
Astrid just messaged me.

15
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:46,833
She sent people to deal
with Emma and Jade.

16
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:51,133
I found out that the couple who
adopted your twins are doctors.

17
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,133
What kind of doctors?

18
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,200
Cardio?

19
00:00:54,267 --> 00:01:04,233
Okay, Sir.

20
00:01:09,233 --> 00:01:19,200
Okay, Sir.

21
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:35,100
Please update us if ever you
find our daughter.

22
00:01:35,167 --> 00:01:36,200
Yes.

23
00:01:36,267 --> 00:01:37,400
Thank you, Sir.

24
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:42,533
Emma, the officers will give us
an update

25
00:01:42,633 --> 00:01:44,367
once they gathered information.

26
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:47,800
Come on.

27
00:01:50,733 --> 00:01:52,500
What if we're too late?

28
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:57,833
What if Olive is mistreating
Mookie?

29
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,733
And I have a bad feeling.

30
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:02,133
What if Olive and Jade
are in this together?

31
00:02:04,033 --> 00:02:07,167
How can you say
that Jade is on it?

32
00:02:07,233 --> 00:02:09,200
She seems like a good person.

33
00:02:09,267 --> 00:02:11,500
She went out of her way
to help us.

34
00:02:11,567 --> 00:02:13,833
What if she's just pretending
to help us?

35
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,533
She might be pretending
to look for information,

36
00:02:15,633 --> 00:02:19,700
but, in reality, she wants to
mislead us

37
00:02:19,767 --> 00:02:22,767
while Olive is taking Mookie
far away from us.

38
00:02:22,833 --> 00:02:24,000
And we won't see her again.

39
00:02:24,067 --> 00:02:26,167
What are we going to do?

40
00:02:26,233 --> 00:02:27,267
Miss Ligaya!

41
00:02:27,333 --> 00:02:29,967
- Let her go! Jade!
- Let me go!

42
00:02:30,033 --> 00:02:31,000
Mom?

43
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:31,733
Mom?

44
00:02:33,267 --> 00:02:34,800
Where are you taking her?

45
00:02:34,867 --> 00:02:37,933
- You monsters!
- Hey! Let me go!

46
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,633
- Miss Ligaya!
- Jade!

47
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:42,733
Why are you doing this?

48
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:43,200
Mom!

49
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:47,167
- Let Jade go!
- Mom!

50
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:48,667
Mom!

51
00:02:53,733 --> 00:02:55,433
- Let me go!
- Jade!

52
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,400
Let her go! Jade!

53
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,367
I need to call for help!

54
00:03:04,433 --> 00:03:06,233
- I can't just stand here!
- I'll do it!

55
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:07,133
I'll call for help!

56
00:03:09,267 --> 00:03:10,467
Are you okay?

57
00:03:11,967 --> 00:03:13,733
Why do you look startled?

58
00:03:17,467 --> 00:03:19,433
Yes, Mommy.

59
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:21,400
I was just surprised.

60
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,733
Oh, no. No, no, no.

61
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,633
You're not surprised.

62
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:27,533
You look scared.

63
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:34,700
Scared to lose the people
you love the most.

64
00:03:34,767 --> 00:03:37,233
Why would I be scared?

65
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:42,567
I don't care about Mommy Emma.

66
00:03:44,100 --> 00:03:46,433
You're the only one I love,
Mommy.

67
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:50,200
Then prove it.

68
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:58,033
We'll see if I really have
your loyalty.

69
00:03:59,567 --> 00:04:01,433
I'll be right back.

70
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:03,333
I'm just gonna bring this
to the kitchen.

71
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:08,733
Behave.

72
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,767
Danilo!

73
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:37,800
Are you okay?

74
00:04:37,867 --> 00:04:41,167
I'm okay. Hurry, Emma!

75
00:04:41,233 --> 00:04:42,400
Danilo!

76
00:04:49,233 --> 00:04:50,400
Ligaya!

77
00:04:51,433 --> 00:04:53,533
Danilo! My God!

78
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,733
Emma!

79
00:04:55,767 --> 00:04:57,400
Emma, hurry!

80
00:04:57,467 --> 00:04:58,033
Over here.
Over there!

81
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:05,767
You monsters!

82
00:05:05,833 --> 00:05:06,500
Please hurry!
- Get them!
- Get them!

83
00:05:07,033 --> 00:05:08,433
Beat them up!

84
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,167
Don't come back.
We will fight you!

85
00:05:10,233 --> 00:05:11,667
Beat them up!

86
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:14,033
Go!

87
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:26,600
- Thank you so much.
- It's okay.

88
00:05:26,667 --> 00:05:27,600
Thank you for helping us.

89
00:05:27,667 --> 00:05:28,733
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

90
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:33,900
- Take care, okay? Okay.
- I'm gonna walk them out.

91
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,533
Okay, thank you.

92
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:38,733
Thank you so much.
Sorry for the trouble.

93
00:05:46,233 --> 00:05:50,167
I'm sorry, my babies,
this is all I can give you.

94
00:05:56,067 --> 00:05:58,400
My babies.  I'm so sorry.

95
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,600
You might be the person
I'm searching for.

96
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:12,800
Perhaps you and Olive
are my twins.

97
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:33,733
I knew it!

98
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:36,000
You're a traitor!

99
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:41,067
You're behind all this,
aren't you?

100
00:06:41,167 --> 00:06:42,700
Me?

101
00:06:42,767 --> 00:06:45,367
Why would you say such a thing?

102
00:06:45,433 --> 00:06:49,167
I almost got hurt, kidnapped,
and beaten up!

103
00:06:49,233 --> 00:06:51,933
And now you're accusing me?

104
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,867
You're jumping to conclusions!

105
00:06:55,933 --> 00:06:57,700
What if you're just making
this all up?

106
00:06:57,767 --> 00:07:02,600
Pretending to get kidnapped
while Mookie's being taken away.

107
00:07:02,667 --> 00:07:03,967
That's the truth behind
all this!

108
00:07:04,033 --> 00:07:07,133
You're talking too much
nonsense!

109
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:08,500
That's enough.

110
00:07:08,567 --> 00:07:09,833
Don't fight.

111
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:11,567
Okay.

112
00:07:11,633 --> 00:07:12,833
Why Mom?

113
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:17,233
Can you stop? Don't start
a fight with Jade. Don't do it.

114
00:07:19,433 --> 00:07:20,733
I'm sorry about that, Jade.

115
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:24,367
You should talk
to your daughter.

116
00:07:24,433 --> 00:07:26,667
What a baseless accusation!

117
00:07:29,433 --> 00:07:30,633
Mom, come over here.

118
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:34,833
Did I hear it right?

119
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:37,400
Are you taking her side?

120
00:07:37,467 --> 00:07:38,933
Mom, I'm your daughter!

121
00:07:40,733 --> 00:07:42,300
You need to know something,
Emma.

122
00:07:46,767 --> 00:07:51,667
I just left for a second,
and now you're texting Emma!

123
00:07:51,767 --> 00:07:53,267
Why?

124
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:56,167
Are you asking her to save you?

125
00:07:56,233 --> 00:07:57,667
No, Mommy.

126
00:07:57,733 --> 00:08:00,367
I just want to surprise you.

127
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:03,533
Look, Mom.

128
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:18,067
Honestly, Mom, I'm content
with what I have now.

129
00:08:18,133 --> 00:08:20,400
I don't wish for anything else.

130
00:08:22,233 --> 00:08:24,100
I just want us to be together.

131
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:29,967
Because I feel safer and happier
with you, Mommy.

132
00:08:40,467 --> 00:08:42,000
You have to hear this, Emma.

133
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:46,667
Jade may be my daughter, too.

134
00:08:48,233 --> 00:08:50,333
What are you talking about?
What nonsense!

135
00:08:52,667 --> 00:08:56,333
She might be one of my twins.

136
00:08:57,867 --> 00:09:00,733
So you shouldn't fight.

137
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:05,100
I have a strong feeling
that you and Jade are sisters.

138
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,867
I'm so sorry, Mookie.

139
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:22,867
I'm so sorry if I doubted you.

140
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:27,400
I'm sorry for accusing you.

141
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:35,900
Mommy!

142
00:09:37,633 --> 00:09:40,400
Your wound might be infected.
You might be bleeding.

143
00:09:41,633 --> 00:09:44,233
We have to go to the hospital.

144
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:46,300
No, no.

145
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:50,667
I can take care of it myself.

146
00:09:50,733 --> 00:09:52,767
Where did you get that idea?

147
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,100
Why are you talking like that?

148
00:09:55,467 --> 00:09:59,933
When I saw Jade and Olive
together...

149
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,100
they reminded me of my twins.

150
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,500
And then I thought...

151
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:10,233
They were the same age
as my twins.

152
00:10:12,533 --> 00:10:15,367
Mom, there are a lot of twins
that have the same birth year!

153
00:10:15,433 --> 00:10:16,733
What are you thinking!

154
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:19,867
Alice called me.

155
00:10:19,933 --> 00:10:22,433
She told me that the couple
who adopted my twins

156
00:10:23,867 --> 00:10:26,300
are cardiologists.

157
00:10:26,367 --> 00:10:27,533
I think that's what
they're called.

158
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:30,300
Then, Jade told me earlier

159
00:10:30,367 --> 00:10:34,467
that their parents are heart
specialists.

160
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:38,767
Mom, we don't even know
if they're adopted!

161
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:40,367
What are you saying?

162
00:10:40,433 --> 00:10:41,833
And look at this.

163
00:10:46,933 --> 00:10:51,533
This is one of the necklace
I gave my twins

164
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,733
before I gave them up
for adoption.

165
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:56,233
I saw Jade wearing this earlier.

166
00:10:57,633 --> 00:10:59,467
I saw this on her.

167
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:06,167
And when that guy hit her,
this fell off from her.

168
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:10,933
Mom, I'm confused.

169
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,200
I'm so confused.

170
00:11:13,133 --> 00:11:14,100
Me too.

171
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,467
I'm confused, too.

172
00:11:16,533 --> 00:11:20,367
I don't know if I should give
this back to her.

173
00:11:22,233 --> 00:11:23,533
I don't know what to do.

174
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,767
I want to ask her a lot
of things.

175
00:11:25,833 --> 00:11:26,633
But I'm...

176
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:30,400
I'm scared.

177
00:11:33,233 --> 00:11:39,800
I'm afraid that she might not
believe me.

178
00:11:39,867 --> 00:11:45,367
What if she believes me
but ends up hating me.

179
00:11:46,733 --> 00:11:49,600
She might hate me
for giving them up.

180
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:51,833
Because I'm a bad mother.

181
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:52,633
Mom!

182
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:58,400
Mom, I know that you're longing
to see my sisters.

183
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:02,533
But it's impossible!
Especially Olive!

184
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,700
She's evil!

185
00:12:07,267 --> 00:12:12,000
Mom, we're here for Mookie.
Her life is in danger.

186
00:12:12,067 --> 00:12:14,767
Can we focus on her for now?

187
00:12:17,433 --> 00:12:20,067
I've been longing for my twins!

188
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:23,533
Emma,

189
00:12:24,833 --> 00:12:26,333
we're both mothers here.

190
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,300
We both long for our children.

191
00:12:29,467 --> 00:12:32,833
So you should understand
what I'm going through.

192
00:12:34,433 --> 00:12:37,233
Don't you remember how you
were with Mookie?

193
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:39,467
You went through drastic
measures for her even

194
00:12:39,533 --> 00:12:41,167
before you found out that
she's your daughter.

195
00:12:41,233 --> 00:12:43,000
I have a proof!

196
00:12:46,267 --> 00:12:50,400
So, please be more understanding
even just a little.

197
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:52,167
Just a little more!

198
00:13:06,133 --> 00:13:07,333
But, mom.

199
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:10,100
You need someone to take care
of you.

200
00:13:13,967 --> 00:13:15,933
I can take care of you.

201
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,367
Just like the old times.

202
00:13:19,467 --> 00:13:20,300
Remember?

203
00:13:22,367 --> 00:13:26,500
As long as you don't tie me up
again.

204
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:59,667
It's a good thing the faucet
is running.

205
00:13:59,733 --> 00:14:01,133
Sorry about that.

206
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:04,900
I washed the cup,
but the water wasn't cold.

207
00:14:04,967 --> 00:14:06,833
Thank you, Ligaya.

208
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:11,100
It's not cold.

209
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:13,033
Thank you.
Thank you.

210
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,567
Ligaya,

211
00:14:22,167 --> 00:14:23,467
are you okay?

212
00:14:24,533 --> 00:14:28,067
Why do you look traumatized?

213
00:14:33,933 --> 00:14:34,900
It's nothing.

214
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:37,500
I'm just tired.

215
00:14:39,767 --> 00:14:41,833
I was so worried about you.

216
00:14:43,767 --> 00:14:44,900
Arigato!

217
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:47,467
I mean, thank you.

218
00:14:49,667 --> 00:14:52,367
Olive is driving me insane!

219
00:14:52,433 --> 00:14:53,800
Can you believe it?

220
00:14:53,867 --> 00:14:58,500
She hired someone to salvage me,
her twin sister!

221
00:14:58,567 --> 00:15:02,733
I'm sure she's behind all this.
No one else is capable of this!

222
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:04,900
Just her, I'm sure of it.

223
00:15:08,767 --> 00:15:10,667
Thank God you're safe.

224
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:15,533
I was so scared!

225
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:18,400
I thought you would get
kidnapped.

226
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:35,033
And also,

227
00:15:38,533 --> 00:15:39,800
I found this.

228
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:46,567
I didn't know I lost this!

229
00:15:46,633 --> 00:15:50,500
Ligaya, thank you so much!
I'm glad you found this.

230
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:53,333
Thank you so much.

231
00:15:54,367 --> 00:15:55,567
Thank you.

232
00:15:55,633 --> 00:15:57,633
I thought I lost it.

233
00:16:00,233 --> 00:16:02,633
Have you had that necklace
for a long time?

234
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:05,400
Very long time.

235
00:16:05,467 --> 00:16:09,333
We had this since
we were babies.

236
00:16:12,700 --> 00:16:14,300
How can this happen, Dan?

237
00:16:14,367 --> 00:16:17,833
How can the person who ruined my
daughter's life be my sister!

238
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:21,667
If your mom is serious
about this.

239
00:16:21,733 --> 00:16:23,133
This could mean trouble.

240
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:25,400
I would feel the same
if I were in your shoes.

241
00:16:25,467 --> 00:16:28,200
To think that the person who did
me wrong is my sister.

242
00:16:28,267 --> 00:16:30,133
I'll be worried, too.

243
00:16:31,367 --> 00:16:33,767
I understand how you feel, Emma.

244
00:16:33,833 --> 00:16:35,733
I understand if you're mad.

245
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:37,733
I'm furious!

246
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:39,333
But I'm scared too, Dan.

247
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:42,700
Having Olive as my sister
is a nightmare!

248
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,733
I can't accept her as my sister.

249
00:16:55,867 --> 00:16:57,533
Who gave you that necklace?

250
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,833
Did your parents give
that to you?

251
00:17:00,067 --> 00:17:01,067
No.

252
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:08,233
Well, they didn't tell us
who gave us this necklace.

253
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:13,200
But before they died,
they told us the truth.

254
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:17,900
They said this necklace came
from our biological parents.

255
00:17:24,633 --> 00:17:26,333
So that means...

256
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:27,800
Yes,

257
00:17:29,467 --> 00:17:31,367
Olive and I are adopted.

258
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:36,467
We're not really from Caparas'
bloodline.

259
00:17:41,067 --> 00:17:41,900
If that's so,

260
00:17:44,533 --> 00:17:48,167
do you know Virgie?

261
00:17:48,267 --> 00:17:49,667
Her name is Virgie Pineda?

262
00:17:51,067 --> 00:17:52,233
No.

263
00:17:53,267 --> 00:17:56,333
She's just someone I know.

264
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:58,633
Are you okay?

265
00:17:58,700 --> 00:17:59,567
Yes, yes, I'm fine.

266
00:18:00,633 --> 00:18:07,533
What year did you get adopted?
How old are you and Olive now?

267
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:12,167
Calm down, okay?
Let's take this slow.

268
00:18:16,067 --> 00:18:21,867
I don't remember what age we
were when we got adopted.

269
00:18:23,133 --> 00:18:27,033
But if you want to know
our age...

270
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:31,133
You have to keep this a secret,
okay?

271
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:34,533
40.

272
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:36,267
We're 40 years old.

273
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:38,100
Can you tell?

274
00:18:47,933 --> 00:18:51,900
You don't know who gave you
away?

275
00:18:51,967 --> 00:18:55,500
You don't know your biological
parents?

276
00:19:02,033 --> 00:19:05,967
You don't know
who gave you away?

277
00:19:06,033 --> 00:19:09,633
You don't know your biological
parents?

278
00:19:13,333 --> 00:19:20,100
Well, Mom and Dad didn't tell us
their name.

279
00:19:20,167 --> 00:19:23,500
But I'm fine with it.

280
00:19:23,567 --> 00:19:28,067
They loved and cared for us,
and that's all that matters.

281
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:33,967
But Olive became bitter.

282
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:37,367
She refused to accept the truth.

283
00:19:39,267 --> 00:19:43,767
She slowly became hateful.

284
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:50,400
Is that why she hurt you before?

285
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:54,600
And now she's hurting Mookie,
my granddaughter.

286
00:20:05,533 --> 00:20:07,500
Are you sure you're okay?

287
00:20:07,567 --> 00:20:08,667
Do you want some water?

288
00:20:08,733 --> 00:20:10,033
- Can I have a drink?
- Okay.

289
00:20:24,167 --> 00:20:26,700
You shocked me with
that revelation.

290
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:29,067
So, are you trying to say that
Olive might be your daughter?

291
00:20:29,133 --> 00:20:31,167
And now you're on bad terms
with Emma.

292
00:20:31,233 --> 00:20:32,433
That's what I'm saying.

293
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:36,500
I've been trying to avoid having
an argument with Emma again.

294
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:40,467
But I can't help it.

295
00:20:40,533 --> 00:20:42,867
Didn't you just make up
with Emma?

296
00:20:42,933 --> 00:20:45,533
And now you're arguing again.

297
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:48,600
My gosh, what a mess!

298
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:51,567
I didn't want this to happen.

299
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:53,633
But what can I do?

300
00:20:53,700 --> 00:20:55,600
I have a strong feeling
about this.

301
00:20:55,667 --> 00:20:56,967
You know me well, right?

302
00:20:57,033 --> 00:20:59,700
My gut feeling always turns out
right.

303
00:20:59,767 --> 00:21:01,933
Especially in gambling, right?

304
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,300
Yes, you're right.

305
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:10,567
But I'm sorry to say this,
we're best of friends...

306
00:21:10,667 --> 00:21:12,800
But Emma has a point.

307
00:21:12,867 --> 00:21:15,433
You don't have enough evidence.

308
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:18,833
Maybe you're longing
for your children.

309
00:21:18,900 --> 00:21:21,600
And that makes you think

310
00:21:21,667 --> 00:21:23,933
that all the twins you see
are your children.

311
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:27,800
You're being emotional, Ligaya.

312
00:21:28,833 --> 00:21:31,133
And why are you insisting
that Olive is your daughter?

313
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:34,567
I thought we hated
that crazy woman, remember?

314
00:21:53,433 --> 00:21:56,400
You're a lot prettier when
you're smiling, Mookie.

315
00:21:58,300 --> 00:22:00,333
I take after you, Mom.

316
00:22:02,867 --> 00:22:05,833
And since we're both pretty
and happy.

317
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:10,267
Especially me,
I'm so, so, happy.

318
00:22:10,333 --> 00:22:12,600
That's why I wanna give you
a treat.

319
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:15,867
What is it?

320
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:21,200
From now on, Mookie, I won't be
a strict mommy anymore.

321
00:22:22,233 --> 00:22:24,767
I will give you everything you
want.

322
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:27,167
Anything you want,
do you want some sweets?

323
00:22:27,233 --> 00:22:29,967
Do you want to watch a movie?
Do you want to go out?

324
00:22:30,033 --> 00:22:32,300
Do you want to watch
your favorite series online?

325
00:22:33,300 --> 00:22:34,267
Really?

326
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:38,600
Can I have some strawberry cake?

327
00:22:38,667 --> 00:22:42,533
I saw it online before.

328
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:44,767
But I'm not allowed to eat it.

329
00:22:44,833 --> 00:22:46,367
That was before.

330
00:22:46,433 --> 00:22:51,000
But from now on, there won't be
any restrictions.

331
00:22:51,100 --> 00:22:53,800
I will give you everything you
want.

332
00:22:54,967 --> 00:22:59,400
And if I can, I will give you
the world.

333
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:03,667
Thank you, Mommy.

334
00:23:41,367 --> 00:23:44,467
If there's nothing here to find,
can we just leave?

335
00:23:44,533 --> 00:23:46,700
My daughter's life could be
in danger.

336
00:23:49,433 --> 00:23:51,400
If you don't want to leave,
then be my guest!

337
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:52,933
Let's go, Mom.

338
00:23:54,033 --> 00:23:54,567
Wait!

339
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:07,467
This is the picture our lawyer
showed us when our parents died.

340
00:24:09,633 --> 00:24:13,100
This is from our biological
mother.

341
00:24:56,967 --> 00:25:01,933
Virgie, can you give this
to their adoptive parents?

342
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,667
What is this?

343
00:25:03,767 --> 00:25:04,700
It's a letter.

344
00:25:05,733 --> 00:25:09,400
I hope my twins will see this
someday.

345
00:25:21,900 --> 00:25:28,900
That's the picture I put in
the envelope.

346
00:25:28,967 --> 00:25:32,400
To give to your adoptive
parents.

347
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:34,400
What?

348
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:45,733
Forgive me, Jade. I'm so sorry.

349
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:50,000
Forgive me for giving you up
when you were a baby.

350
00:25:51,100 --> 00:25:53,667
I know that you won't forgive me
after this.

351
00:25:54,733 --> 00:25:58,233
I'm sorry that I have to do
this to you.

352
00:25:58,300 --> 00:25:59,767
I want to be free.

353
00:25:59,833 --> 00:26:02,200
I want to be strong.
And I want to be happy.

354
00:26:03,233 --> 00:26:04,733
With my mom, Emma.

355
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:07,100
I can accept Jade as my sister.

356
00:26:07,167 --> 00:26:10,000
But I can never accept Olive!

357
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:12,400
I can't even accept her
as a person!

358
00:26:12,467 --> 00:26:13,533
Okay, fine!

359
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:16,833
She's a horrible person,
I know that!

360
00:26:16,900 --> 00:26:18,967
But she's my daughter!
She's a human being!

361
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:21,967
Where are you going?

362
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:25,367
Did you put something
on my food?
